# Copy to `.envrc.local` and edit for the host. This file is the template;
# `.envrc.local` itself is gitignored.
#
# Two flavors of host appear in practice:
#   - NixOS / nix-shell: needs explicit nix-store paths so cargo, rustc, and
#     binaryninja can find libstdc++ / libclang / openssl.
#   - Stock Linux (Arch, Debian, …): usually nothing here at all. BINJA_PATH
#     is the only knob most boxes need.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Where Binary Ninja lives. Used to find libbinaryninjacore.so.1.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# export BINJA_PATH="$HOME/down/binja/binaryninja-commerical/binaryninja"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. NixOS-only: dynamic discovery of compiler libs the build needs at runtime.
#    Skip this whole block on stock Linux distros.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
